---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const appName     = "Gratefuly";
const lastUpdated = "March 2026";
const contactEmail = "hello@wiplabs.app";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Terms of Use — ${appName}`}
  description={`Terms of Use for ${appName} by WIPLabs.`}
>
  <style>
    /* ── Hero ── */
    .policy-hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5C8A6E, #7EC8A0);
      padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .policy-hero .emoji { font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block; }
    .policy-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .policy-hero p {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ── Page body ── */
    .policy-page { padding: 4rem 0; max-width: 720px; }
    .meta { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .policy-page h2 {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .policy-page p  { color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .policy-page ul { color: var(--text-muted); padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .policy-page a  { color: var(--accent); }

    .back-link {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

    hr { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin: 2rem 0; }
  </style>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="policy-hero">
    <span class="emoji">🌿</span>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p>Gratefuly — Daily Gratitude Journal</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="container">
    <div class="policy-page">
      <a href="/apps/gratefuly" class="back-link">← Back to {appName}</a>

      <p class="meta">{appName} · WIPLabs · Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By downloading or using Gratefuly ("the App"), you agree to be bound by these
        Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the App.
        These terms apply to all users of the App.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        Gratefuly is a personal journaling application that helps users practice gratitude
        through daily prompts, mood tracking, and media attachments. The App stores all
        user data locally on the user's device.
      </p>

      <h2>3. License</h2>
      <p>
        WIPLabs grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license
        to use the App for your personal, non-commercial purposes. You may not:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Copy, modify, or distribute the App</li>
        <li>Reverse engineer or attempt to extract the source code</li>
        <li>Use the App for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Sell, rent, or sublicense the App</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Premium Subscriptions & In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Gratefuly offers optional premium features through in-app purchases processed by
        Apple's App Store. The following terms apply to premium subscriptions:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Monthly & Yearly subscriptions</strong> automatically renew unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
        <li><strong>Lifetime purchase</strong> is a one-time payment granting permanent access to premium features.</li>
        <li>Subscriptions can be managed and cancelled in your Apple ID account settings.</li>
        <li>No refunds are provided for partial subscription periods unless required by applicable law.</li>
        <li>Prices may change with notice provided through the App or App Store.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. User Content</h2>
      <p>
        You retain full ownership of all content you create within the App, including journal
        entries, photos, voice recordings, and videos. Since all content is stored locally
        on your device, WIPLabs does not access, use, or claim any rights over your content.
      </p>
      <p>
        You are responsible for maintaining backups of your data. WIPLabs is not responsible
        for any loss of data resulting from device failure, loss, or deletion of the App.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree to use Gratefuly only for lawful purposes. You must not use the App to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Store or share illegal content</li>
        <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
        <li>Infringe on the rights of others</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        The free version of Gratefuly displays advertisements through Google AdMob.
        By using the free version, you agree to the display of ads. Premium subscribers
        receive an ad-free experience.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.
        WIPLabs does not warrant that the App will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free
        of viruses or other harmful components. We do not warrant the accuracy or
        completeness of any content within the App.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, WIPLabs shall not be liable for
        any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including
        loss of data, arising out of or related to your use of the App.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to discontinue the App or any of its features at any time.
        You may stop using the App at any time by deleting it from your device.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable laws.
        Any disputes arising from these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction
        of the competent courts.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms of Use from time to time. Continued use of the App after
        changes constitutes your acceptance of the new terms. We will update the "Last updated"
        date at the top of this page when changes are made.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about these Terms of Use, please contact us at:
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>
      </p>

      <hr />
      <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
        © 2026 WIP Labs · <a href="https://wiplabs.app">wiplabs.app</a>
        · <a href="/apps/gratefuly/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>